                <p>People who are thinking of flying with Frontier Airlines but are not sure about the baggage policy and size rules are in the right place. Here is everything you need to know about the baggage policy and personal items. This blog is all about the personal items in <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/frontier-airlines.aspx"><b>Frontier Airlines</b></a>, and through this blog, you can know the size requirements and other rules. <b>Frontier Airlines personal items size</b> is 14 inches x 18 inches x 8 inches, and you should follow this policy and size requirement. Then it is good for you to avoid any other extra charges. The airline is known for the low-cost fares and this is the reason the size and fee are quite strict of the airline.</p>
                <h2>What Is a Personal Item on Frontier Airlines?</h2>
                <p>A personal item is a small piece of luggage or accessory that passengers are allowed to bring onboard without any additional fee. This is not the type of checked or carry-on luggage, and your item must meet the strict size requirements to qualify as a free item.</p>
                <h3>Examples of personal items include:</h3>
                <p>A purse or handbag</p>
